-----------------------------------------------------------------
  toshiba_DPall-0  - all dual-prime MP@ML bitstream 
                     for Video Conformance Testing  (ID=3)
-----------------------------------------------------------------

Bitstream ID:   3.
Description:    All dual-prime macroblocks in frame-coded picture
Stresses:       prediction bandwidth
Justification:  prediction bandwidth is at a maximum in this mode
Parameters:     Main Level, 4 frames
Organizations:  Toshiba

Included files:

        - toshiba_DPall-0.mpg     248077 byte : bitstream file
        - toshiba_DPall-0.frame  2073600 byte : reconstructed frames*

       *Data format     +----720----+
                        |           |
                      480     Y     |
                        | (#1frame) |
                        +-----+-----+
                      240 Cb#1|
                        +-----+
                      240 Cr#1|
                        +-360-+-----+
                        | Y(#2frame)|

Parameters:

        - Profile      : MP@ML based on DIS (25 March 1994)
        - bit_rate     : 15 Mbps
        - dimensions   : 720 x 480
        - frame_rate   : 30 Hz
        - structure    : IPPP (frame-pictures)
        - MC mode      : All dual-prime (P-pictures)
	- q_scale_type : 1 (non-linear)
        - VBV buffer   : 1.75 Mbit (1,835,008 bits)
        - image        : mobile & calendar

Note: To examine the real-time decoding ability of MPEG-2 decoders
in a worse case, the number of generated bits of the 3rd picture 
is set close to the VBV buffer size, and most of them is allocated 
to the upper side MBs. In the 3rd picture, you can find ONE big MB 
that contains more then 4608 bits. This bitstream meets the VBV 
constraints.

